post_text:
The Stakeholder Team (40+members) continues working hard on Reopening Plans for Lind-Ritzville Cooperative Schools. To help school districts with the process, OSPI is scheduled to release a planning template this week. We are still planning for the return of all students on August 31st. Students returning to On-Campus Learning will need to meet all health and safety requirements which includes daily health screenings, social distancing, and wearing a mask. There are many parts to this, extremely flexible, plan that must be in place before it can be approved by school boards and submitted to the State for final authorization. We will continue to share more information as it becomes available. Thank-you very much for your remarkable patience and support.

Don Vanderholm
Superintendent

Facility Use During the COVID School Closure

It is our hope to keep the Ritzville District Track open for public use during the current State of Emergency. Those using the track must adhere to social distancing guidelines. Reminder that bicycles are not allowed on the track. Inappropriate use of this facility will result in temporary closure. All other facilities, including gymnasiums and weight rooms remain closed until further notice. Thank you for your understanding and cooperation.

shared_text:
Silverwood Read 2 Ride
April 6 at 2:00 PM ¬∑

As students begin to finish up their 10 hours of reading, we are receiving some questions regarding how they turn in their logs since they aren't in school. We are asking that parents email their student's teacher either a scan or a picture of their child's completed reading log. The teacher will then confirm that the 10-hour goal was met and then award the student their ticket in the teacher's dashboard. After the ticket has been awarded, the teacher can either print or email the ticket to the student. Reminder: reading logs are due by April 30th and teachers can award tickets until May 15th. Thank you for reading!!

THANK-YOU!

Dear Citizens of the Lind School District and the Ritzville School District,

On behalf of both School Boards, the staff, and administration I want to thank you very much for your generous support in passing the levy proposals put before you on February 11th. Because of you, we can continue to provide quality programs for our kids, maintain our outstanding facilities, and keep building our two wonderful communities.

With much appreciation!
Superintendent Don Vanderholm

post_text: Congratulations to our LRMS FFA members on their achievements in Livestock Judging and Horse Judging at the Othello Fair. Alyssa and Megan were on the LR FFA Livestock team that place 5th overall out of well over 60 teams. Our first time horse judging team comprised of all LRMS FFA members, Claire , Addy, Alyssa, and Piper did very well also. Claire placed 2nd individual out of over 200 students! Good job everyone!

The FFA Floral team had great success in Mt. Baker this weekend!!
The LR Gold team placed 3rd and the LR Blue team 5th.
Amy Anderson placed 1st individually, Alexis Melcher 5th, Annika Holland 8th, and Grace Saint John almost reached the top 10 and placed 11th.
Both teams also placed in every area of the contest (tool/plant ID, problem solving, general knowledge, and individual practicum).
Gold team: Amy Anderson, Annika Holland, Michael Nichols, Levi Hoeft, Alexus Crombie.
Blue team: Alexis Melcher, Grace Saint John, Raegan Snider.
Way to go teams!!üíõüíô
